("SS3101",5,"E-BUSINESS CAPSTONE PROJECT","This module is offered as part of the CP3101 Topics in Computing series. It introduces software development on the web. Topics include networking, clients and servers, HTTP protocol and HTML5 localStorage, HTML5 forms, CSS, dynamically served pages using PHP, DOM, Object Oriented Javascript and jQuery, and combining Javascript and PHP to build an AJAX web application. We will also investigate the use of Javascript, HTML5 canvas, sensor API and mobile platform to build responsive mobile. Some advanced topics may be discussed such as web security and how to generate traffic to your web application. More Details are on the CP3101B website .",160,"aaaaaaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa"),
